.TH RECONFORGE 1 "March 2026" "v1.0.0" "ReconForge Manual"
.SH NAME
reconforge \- Comprehensive Web Vulnerability Meta Scanner
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B reconforge
[\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B ReconForge
is a Python-based web vulnerability meta scanner that automates Dynamic Application Security Testing (DAST). It orchestrates multiple security scanners (Nuclei, Nikto, Wapiti, ZAP, Skipfish) and aggregates their results into a single vulnerability report. By default, it runs in verbose mode showing all scanner output.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-t ", " \-\-target " \fIURL\fR"
Target URL to scan (e.g., https://example.com). This option is required.
.TP
.BR \-S ", " \-\-scanners " \fISCANNER_LIST\fR"
Space-separated list of scanners to run. Options: nuclei, nikto, wapiti, zap, skipfish. Default is all.
.TP
.BR \-si ", " \-\-silent
Silent mode. Hide scanner output and show a progress bar instead.
.TP
.BR \-o ", " \-\-output\-dir " \fIDIR\fR"
Directory to save scan results. Default is 'reports'.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Display help message and exit.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
.B reconforge -t https://example.com
Run all scanners against example.com in verbose mode.
.TP
.B reconforge -t https://example.com -si
Run all scanners against example.com in silent mode with a progress bar.
.TP
.B reconforge -t https://example.com -S nuclei zap
Run only Nuclei and ZAP scanners.
